From: Gary Keim <gk5g+@andrew.cmu.edu>
Subject: solved: flex problem
Date: Sun, 22 Aug 1993 16:07:25 -0400

I fixed my problem with flex by changing the declaration of yytext from:

extern char yytext[];

---->

extern char *yytext;

The flexdocs man page talks about this in the section describing the
differences between flex, lex, and POSIX.

Another question:  for completeness, it would be nice if there existed
/usr/lib/libl.a that pointed at /usr/lib/libfl.a, just as lex points to
flex.

-Gary Keim
Andrew Consortium



